1.6 "Licensed SpinCo IP" refers to (i) the SpinCo Intellectual Property, excluding Trademark-Related IP, the SpinCo Software, and the SpinCo Technology, and all rights, interests, and claims of either Party or any of its affiliates as of the Effective Time pertaining to Information that is exclusively related to the items specified in clause (i), subject to the restrictions stated herein and to the extent controlled by SpinCo or any member of the SpinCo Group at the Effective Time (including through the assignments made under this Agreement). The Licensed SpinCo IP does not include:

(a) SpinCo Intellectual Property, SpinCo Software, SpinCo Technology, or Intellectual Property related to chemically activated carbon products or any processes for manufacturing such products (for clarification, including activated carbon sheets);
(b) SpinCo-owned Intellectual Property pertaining to ex-mill processes for purifying crude tall oil and isolating, purifying, and derivatizing lignin from black liquor or any products created using such processes;
(c) Intellectual Property licensed to Alberdingk Boley, Inc. ("ABI"), except where it falls outside the "Field," as defined in the "License Agreement" dated February 3, 2006, between MeadWestvaco Corporation and ABI;
(d) Intellectual Property owned by Purification Cellutions, LLC, a joint venture between MeadWestvaco Corporation and Applied Ceramics, Inc.;
(e) Intellectual Property or processes for manufacturing products utilizing specialty chemicals derived from co-products of the kraft pulping process that SpinCo sells into the paper or packaging field, including paper sizing;
(f) any third-party owned Intellectual Property (comprising joint ventures, partnerships, or similar business entities in which SpinCo is a member or holds an ownership interest), unless it can be sublicensed to Parent or any of its affiliates by SpinCo or any member of the SpinCo Group.
